sections.body:
`sort` has the following syntax:

```json
{
  "$search": {
    "index": "<index name>", // optional, defaults to "default"
    "<operator>": { // such as "text", "compound", or "phrase"
      <operator-specification>
    },
    "sort": {
      score: {$meta: "searchScore"}, // optional field
      "<field-to-sort>": <sort-order>, // 1 or -1, or a document
      ...
    }
  }
}
```

| Parameter        | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| ---------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| score            | Optional. Determines whether to sort by the search score. To learn more, see Sort by Score And a Unique Field.                                                                                                                                                                               |
| \<field-to-sort> | Required. The name of the field to sort by.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| \<sort-order>    | Required. Determines the sort order. Use 1 for ascending order and -1 for descending order.If you want to specify the noData field, use a document with the following syntax:"\<field-to-sort>": \{ order: 1 \| -1, // required field noData: "lowest" \| "highest" // optional field }, ... |

