The following query on the `sample_mflix.movies` namespace uses the
[$search](pipe.$search) stage to do the following:

- Search for movies that have the term `country` in the title.

- Sort the results in ascending order using `sort` option.

The query uses the [$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) stage to limit the output to `5`
documents. It also uses the [$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to do the
following:

- Omit all fields except `title` in the results.

- Add a field named `score`.

**Input:**

```json
db.movies.aggregate([
  {
    "$search": {
      "text": {
        "path": "title",
        "query": "country"
      },
      "sort": {
        "title": 1
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "$limit": 5
  },
  {
    "$project": {
      "_id": 0,
      "title": 1,
      "score": { "$meta": "searchScore" }
    }
  }
])
```

