The following query shows how to sort the results regardless of the
letter case. It uses the [text](text-ref) operator to search for
movies that have the term `train` in the `title` field and then
sorts the results by the `title` field value in ascending order.The query specifies a [$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) stage to limit the documents
in the results to `5` and a [$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to do the
following:* Include only the `_id`, `title`, and `awards` fields in the
  results.

