    c: ObjectId('507f1f77bcf86cd799439011'),
    score: 0.025981096550822258
  },
  { _id: 1, c: true, score: 0.025981096550822258 }
]
```The order of documents with `"_id": 4`, `"_id": 5`, `"_id": 6`, and `"_id": 7`
is random because MongoDB Search treats null and missing values as equal
when sorting.**Descending-sort:**Descending SortFor a descending sort, MongoDB Search uses the element with the
highest BSON (Binary Javascript Object Notation) type to represent the multi-typed array.
MongoDB Search uses `false` to represent the multi-typed array for
the document with `_id: 7`, as this is the highest BSON (Binary Javascript Object Notation) type
in the array. Since MongoDB Search also ranks `true` values above `false` values,
MongoDB Search returns this document after the document with `_id: 1`.To learn more, see [Sort by Null and Missing Values](fts-sort-null) and
[Sort Arrays with Multiple Types](fts-sort-arrays-multiple-types).**Input:**```json
db.users.aggregate([
